      <hazardstatement type="caution">
         <messagepanel>
            <typeofhazard>UNAUTHORIZED ACCESS</typeofhazard>
            <howtoavoid>Always change your user passwords after the first login.
When selecting a new password follow your siteâ€™s security protocols
and the password criteria in the chapter Change Passwords.</howtoavoid>
         </messagepanel>
      </hazardstatement>
      <p>The system is delivered with the default passwords. Change the
default passwords directly after the first login.</p>
      <p>It is recommended to store the new passwords in a secure way so
that they are not forgotten, for example by using a password manager.</p>
